# Docs generated from Cursor (rules, skills, commands)

This repository builds its VitePress site from Cursor sources by using **`docs/scripts/generate-docs.mjs`**. The generated content lives under **`docs/src/`**, and the generated sidebar lives in **`docs/.vitepress/sidebar.generated.mts`**.

When working on this docs system, install and use the **`vitepress-cursor-docs`** skill if it is available in your skill environment. If needed, install it with **`npx skills add OmicoDev/skills --skill vitepress-cursor-docs`**.

## What not to edit

Do not hand-edit these generated output directories:

- **`docs/src/cursor-rules/`** — from `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
- **`docs/src/cursor-commands/`** — from `.cursor/commands/*.md`
- **`docs/src/agent-skills/`** — from `.cursor/skills/**` (SKILL.md and references)

Also avoid editing these generated outputs by hand:

- **`docs/.vitepress/sidebar.generated.mts`** — generated sidebar data
- Generated section index pages such as **`docs/src/cursor-rules/index.md`**

The site homepage, such as **`docs/src/index.md`**, may still be hand-maintained unless another rule or local convention says otherwise.

## Editing content

- To change generated docs content, edit the **source** files under `.cursor/rules`, `.cursor/commands`, or `.cursor/skills`.
- After editing source files, run **`npm run docs:prepare`** from the repo root or from `docs/`.
- The same prepare step runs automatically before `docs:dev` and `docs:build`.
- Generated section index pages use a Markdown `#` heading only and do not include a `title` frontmatter block.

## Changing nav or sidebar

- **Nav** is defined in **`docs/.vitepress/config.mts`** under `themeConfig.nav`. Edit that file to add or reorder top-level nav links.
- **Sidebar** is generated into **`docs/.vitepress/sidebar.generated.mts`**. To change sidebar structure, update **`docs/scripts/generate-docs.mjs`** instead of editing the generated file.
- Typical sidebar changes happen in `FLAT_SECTIONS` or in the agent-skills sidebar generation logic, followed by **`npm run docs:prepare`**.

## CI and deployment

- The **Deploy docs** workflow in **`.github/workflows/docs.yml`** runs on pushes to `main` when matching docs-related paths change.
- Source changes under `.cursor/commands/*.md`, `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc`, `.cursor/skills/**/*.md`, and changes under `docs/**` already trigger a docs rebuild and deploy.
- If you add a new source directory that the generator should include, wire it into **`generate-docs.mjs`** and update the workflow `paths` filter if the new directory is outside the existing watched paths.
